{{Japanese kana | kana = ら | sound = <big style="font-size: 150%;">{{audio|Ra (Japanese).ogg|'''ra'''}}</big> | mnemonic = The face of someone enjoying the smell of their '''ra'''men. Draw his eyebrow first, then his nose and mouth. It looks like a '''ra'''ttled number five. | example = * らくだ (rakuda) camel * らっぱ (rappa) trumpet * らば (raba) mule }} {{Japanese kana | kana = り | sound = <big style="font-size: 150%;">{{audio|Ri (Japanese).ogg|'''ri'''}}</big> | mnemonic = *It's the nose and cheek of '''Ri'''chard. *It's a '''re'''peat (ri) of い (i) with the lengths of the lines inversed. | example = * りんご (ringo) apple * りす (risu) squirrel * りゅう (ryuu) dragon }} '''Note:''' The handwritten form varies slightly from the printed form り {{Japanese kana | kana = る | sound = <big style="font-size: 150%;">{{audio|Ru (Japanese).ogg|'''ru'''}}</big> | mnemonic = * The arm and closed fist of a student who has to hold buckets of water out in the hall because he broke the '''ru'''les. * A boat hit a message in a '''ru'''m bottle (the upper part being the boat, the lower the corked bottle). *It's a mouth, and it's '''ru'''de to eat with your mouth open. * Follow your money as it floats down into the toilet and is flushed, which you '''rue'''. | example = * るす (rusu) absency (from home) * るい (rui) class * るつぼ (rutsubo) melting pot }} {{Japanese kana | kana = れ | sound = <big style="font-size: 150%;">{{audio|Re (Japanese).ogg|'''re'''}}</big> | mnemonic = * The ''t'' on the left is the end of a pier, and its builder '''re'''commends replacing it. * You can distinguish it from [[Japanese/Kana/Lessons/Hiragana/Lesson 5|ね]] and [[Japanese/Kana/Lessons/Hiragana/Lesson 10|わ]] because it has the tip of the second wave, visible on the right | example = * れきし (rekishi) history * れいそく (reisoku) your son * れい (rei) spirit, ghost }} {{Japanese kana | kana = ろ | sound = <big style="font-size: 150%;">{{audio|Ro (Japanese).ogg|'''ro'''}}</big> | mnemonic = * It's the front tip of a '''row''' boat riding a wave. * It's the tail and hindquarter of a '''ro'''aring lion. * You can distinguish it from る because 'ro' doesn't have the circle at the bottom; the 'o' is in 'ro', not in its character. | example = * ろく (roku) six * ろうそく (rousoku) candle * ろんぶん (ronbun) essay, thesis, dissertation }}
