{{Template:Japanese kana navigation}} In this lesson you are going to learn how to read and write カ、キ、ク、ケ、コ. Adding two small lines called {{furi|濁|だく}}{{furi|点|てん}} ''dakuten'', but commonly known simply as {{furi|点々|てんてん}} ''tenten'', meaning "two marks", causes clear sounds to change to their voiced sound. Thus, adding the {{furi|点々|てんてん}} ''tenten'' marks will cause カ、キ、ク、ケ、コ to be produced ガ、ギ、グ、ゲ、ゴ.
{{Japanese kana | kana = カ | sound = <big><big>ka</big></big> | mnemonic = Like the か (ka) of Hiragana, just missing the extra stroke on the right. | example = * カナダ (kanada) Canada * カメラ (kamara) camera * カカオ (kakao) cacao | voiced = ガ | voiced_sound = <big><big>ga</big></big> | voiced_example = * ガラパゴス (garapagosu) Galapagos * ガイダンス (gaidansu) guidance * ガバナンス (gabanansu) governance }} {{Japanese kana | kana = キ | sound = <big><big>ki</big></big> | mnemonic = Another '''key''', now just the top half. | example = * キルギズタン (kirugizustan) Kyrgyzstan * キウイ (kiui) kiwi * キス (kisu) kiss | voiced = ギ | voiced_sound = <big><big>gi</big></big> | voiced_example = * ギア (gia) gear * ギアナ (giana) Guiana * ギフト (gifuto) gift }} {{Japanese kana | kana = ク | sound = <big><big>ku</big></big> | mnemonic = * The open wing of a '''coo'''ing pigeon. * The handle of a '''cu'''p * '''Coo'''kie with a bite taken out of it, held in the lower left corner. | example = * クウェート (kueeto) Kuwait * クリック (kurikku) click * クローン (kuroon) clone | voiced = グ | voiced_sound = <big><big>gu</big></big> | voiced_example = * グアバ (guaba) guava * グリーン (guriin) green * グアム (guamu) Guam }} {{Japanese kana | kana = ケ | sound = <big><big>ke</big></big> | mnemonic = * Looks like a "K" tilted to the side. Just pronounce the K with a Japanese accent so its "ke". * You '''gue'''ssed wrong. This isn't a pigeon wing but a bat wing, because it has a claw; the bat lives in a '''ca'''ve | example = * ケベック (kebekku) Quebec * ケーブル (keeburu) cable * ケーキ (keeki) cake | voiced = ゲ | voiced_sound = <big><big>ge</big></big> | voiced_example = * ゲゲゲ (gegege) sound used to signify cackling * ゲノム (genomu) genome * ゲリラセン (gerirasen) guerilla warfare }} {{Japanese kana | kana = コ | sound = <big><big>ko</big></big> | mnemonic = * Like the hiragana こ, but connected at the right hand side. The bottom stroke was to be a '''co'''py of the top one but ran out of room. * It's the side-view of a '''go'''pher's burrow. * Looks like the '''co'''rners of the edge of a table. | example = * コンゴ (kongo) Congo * コーヒー (koohii) coffee * コンピュータ (konpyuuta) computer | voiced = ゴ | voiced_sound = <big><big>go</big></big> | voiced_example = * ゴブレット (goburetto) goblet * ゴブリン (goburin) goblin * ゴジラ (gojira) Godzilla }}
