{{Template:Japanese kana navigation}} This page introduces "ハ", "ヒ", "フ", "ヘ" and "ホ". Adding two short lines, the ''dakuten'' ({{furi|濁|だく}}{{furi|点|てん}}) or, more informally, ''tenten'' ({{furi|点々|てんてん}}) meaning "two marks", to create "バ", "ビ", ""ブ", "ベ" and "ボ" changes clear sounds to voiced ones. Adding a small circle called a {{furi|半|>はん}}{{furi|濁|だく}}{{furi|点|てん}} ''handakuten'', but commonly referred to as ''maru'' ({{furi|丸|まる}}) meaning "circle", written "パ", "ピ", "プ", "ペ" and "ポ" changes clear sounds plosive sound.
